<!--
  ════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
  NaukariPhoto catalog — single source of truth for every exam & service.

  HOW TO ADD A NEW EXAM OR SERVICE
  ─────────────────────────────────
  1. Copy one <entry> block below (an exam or a service) and paste it
     before the closing </catalog> tag.
  2. Change the `id` to something unique, lowercase, no spaces (e.g. "cmat").
  3. Set `type` to "exam" or "service".
  4. Set `name` — this is ALL that shows on the card (e.g. "JEE Main").
     Do not put full forms here; that goes in <fullName>, which is only
     shown inside the expanded detail view, not on the card.
  5. Set `logo` to a file under /public/logos/ (any png/svg/jpg/webp).
     Drop your image file into public/logos/ with that exact filename —
     no code changes needed.
  6. Set `color` (used for accents) and `bg` (used for the card background
     when active) as hex values.
  7. List each required document under <documents>. For every <document>:
       - id        → unique within this entry
       - label     → shown to the user
       - type      → one of: photo | signature | id | document
                     (controls which icon renders — see iconMap in code)
       - required  → true | false
       - format    → accepted file formats, comma separated (e.g. "JPG,PNG")
       - minSizeKB / maxSizeKB → file size bounds in kilobytes
       - <dimensions> → at least ONE of <px> or <physical> must be present.
             <px width="..." height=".../>                — pixel-exact spec
             <physical width="..." height="..." unit="cm|inch" dpi="..."/>
                                                            — physical spec
         If both are present, <px> is treated as authoritative and
         <physical> is shown as a secondary reference (handy when the
         exam's own notification states cm/inch instead of px).
       - background (optional) → expected photo background, free text
  8. That's it — the UI (cards, expanded view, document checklist) is
     entirely generated from this file. No component code needs to change.
  ════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
-->
<catalog>

